---
import SectionContainer from "../../components/ui/SectionContainer.astro";
import CTAGroup from "../../components/ui/CTAGroup.astro";
---

<section class="bg-[#04101f] py-20 md:py-24">
  <SectionContainer>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,0.95fr)_minmax(0,1.05fr)] gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-center">
      <div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
        <div class="max-w-xl">
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">
            Why Most Google Ads Appeals Fail — And What Google Actually Looks For
          </h2>

          <p class="mt-5 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/72">
            Most advertisers submit appeals that are emotional, vague, or incomplete.
            Google reviewers are looking for structured explanations supported by policy-aligned evidence.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-8 space-y-6">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-white">
                Google Suspensions Are Based on Risk Signals
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] leading-7 text-white/68">
                Google assesses advertiser risk across website, verification, payment, and historical account signals.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-white">
                Google Expects Structured, Policy-Aligned Appeals
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] leading-7 text-white/68">
                Appeals need policy references, corrective actions, and documentation that demonstrates compliance.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-white">
                Repeated Appeals Can Make Recovery More Difficult
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] leading-7 text-white/68">
                Multiple failed submissions can reduce the likelihood of a meaningful review and trigger faster automated responses.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-white">
                Google Reviews More Than Just Ads
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] leading-7 text-white/68">
                The issue may sit in the website, account structure, verification data, or payment setup rather than ad copy alone.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold text-white">
                Not Every Suspended Account Can Be Recovered
              </h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-[15px] leading-7 text-white/68">
                Some suspensions result in permanent restrictions, which is why viability should be assessed before further submissions.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="mt-10">
            <CTAGroup />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[560px]">
          <img
            src="/images/suspension-stress.webp"
            alt="Suspended advertiser reviewing a failed Google Ads appeal"
            class="w-full rounded-[28px] border border-white/10 object-cover"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </SectionContainer>
</section>